# Backend (Strapi 5)

## Conventions

- Use **TypeScript** for all backend code.
- Content-types and APIs live in `back/src/api/`: one folder per entity (content-types, controllers, routes, services). Follow Strapi 5 conventions.

## API structure

- `back/src/api/<name>/content-types/<name>/schema.json` — content-type schema.
- Controllers, routes, services live in the respective subfolders of `back/src/api/<name>/`.

## Rules for the AI

- When adding or changing content-types, update files in `back/src/api/`, not only via the Strapi admin UI (so that changes stay in code and in the repository).
- Use the current APIs and folder structure of Strapi 5.
